McDonalds will give free coffee to customers across Northern California as of January 2

Branches of McDonalds in Northern California are to give away free cups of coffee to 'offer a helping hand at the start of the new year'.

From January 2, all local branches of the fast food chain throughout Northern California will offer a free small Premium Roast Coffee with no purchase necessary.

McDonalds say the initiative is a way of saying 'thank you', and to give customers a helping hand in the new year.

