'As the holiday season comes to a close and budgets become tight, we hope this program will offer some comfort to our community and also warm them up a little during this cold, winter season.

McDonalds' free coffee programme will last for two weeks across 14 counties in Northern California.

The programme is not the first time McDonalds has given away free coffee to customers in American.

In Apil, the chain gave coffee away to diners at its Western Washington drive-through locations for two weeks.

The participating counties are: Sacramento, Placer, Nevada, Sutter, Yuba, Yolo, El Dorado (not including S. Lake Tahoe restaurants), Solano (not including restaurants west of Fairfield), San Joaquin, Stanislaus, Amador, Calaveras, Tuolumne and Colusa.

